PuTTY is a free software application for Windows 95, 98, XP, Vista, and 7 which can be used to make an SSH connection to your server. In order to make this connection establishment, please do the following steps:

1.Download PuTTY from http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/ or another PuTTY download source.

2.Double-click on the putty.exe program to launch the application.

3. Enter your connection settings


- Host Name: IP address
- Port: 22 (leave as default)
- Connection Type: SSH (leave as default)

4.Click Open to start the SSH session.

5.Once the SSH Connection is open, you should see a terminal prompt asking for your username and password. Please note that you will NOT see your cursor moving, or any characters typed (such as ******), when typing your password. This is a standard PuTTY security feature. Hit enter.

6.You are now logged into your server with SSH.
